title: Dugganite (Pb$_{3}$Zn$_{3}$TeAs$_{2}$O$_{14}$) Structure
comments: Some authors use langasite, Ca$_{3}$Ga$_{2}$Ge$_{4}$O$_{14}$ or La$_{3}$Ga$_{4}$(Ga,Si)$_{4}$O$_{14}$, as the prototype for this structure, however in langasite the (1a) and (3f) Wyckoff positions are a mixture of gallium and germanium atoms (Dudka, 2013).  None of the Wyckoff positions in dugganite are disordered, so we use it as the prototype.
